				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you're just making a plug-in, and you don't expect compatibility with NES ROMs or NSF files, you can simplify the model by always using the constant volume mode. Let the instrument define the channel's output from 0 to 15 and change it 60 times a second.<br /><br />Likewise you can mostly ignore the sweep units. Let controller messages (portamento, pitch bend) and your modulation LFO change the period every frame.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

